name: geranylgeranyl diphosphate synthase
classes: Transferring alkyl or aryl groups, other than methyl groups;
Transferring alkyl or aryl groups, other than methyl groups (only sub-subclass identified to date)
reaction: (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate + isopentenyl diphosphate = diphosphate + geranylgeranyl diphosphate [RN:R02061]
comment: Some forms of this enzyme will also use geranyl diphosphate and dimethylallyl diphosphate as donors; it will not use larger prenyl diphosphates as efficient donors.

references.title: Occurrence and unusual properties of geranylgeranyl pyrophosphate synthetase of pig liver.
